# === THE ONE MANUAL STEP ===
# 1. Copy this file to `.env`   ->   cp .env.example .env
# 2. Paste your GitHub Copilot access-token below (the ONLY thing you do by hand).
#
# Get the token from a machine that's already working:
#     cat ~/.config/litellm/github_copilot/access-token
# It starts with  ghu_  (or gho_).
#
# PASTE IT RAW: no surrounding quotes, no trailing spaces. If you edit this file on
# Windows, save it with LF line endings (a CRLF \r will corrupt the token silently;
# the installer strips it anyway, but LF is safest).
#
# This seeds the proxy so the new machine does NOT need a GitHub OAuth/2FA login.
# It's your own token on your own device.

COPILOT_ACCESS_TOKEN=

# ---- optional ----
# Pin the local gateway password (guards only the 127.0.0.1:4000 proxy; NOT a real
# secret). If unset, a random one is generated and reused across runs.
# LITELLM_MASTER_KEY=

# Force a runtime. Default is native Python (most reliable on a fresh Mac); Docker is
# used only if you set this to docker or already have a running docker engine.
# NOTE: the --python / --docker command-line flags OVERRIDE this line.
# RUNTIME=docker
# RUNTIME=python
